[1] China - China National Health Commission 5 Feb 2020
Date: Wed 5 Feb 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [in Chinese, machine trans., edited]
http://www.nhc.gov.cn/xcs/yqtb/202002/17a03704a99646ffad6807bc806f37a4.shtml


Update on pneumonia of new coronavirus infections as of 24:00, 4 Feb 2020
--------------------------------------------------------------------
At 04:00 on [4 Feb 2020], 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 3887 newly confirmed cases (3156 cases in Hubei Province), and 431 new severe cases (377 cases in Hubei Province). There was an increase of 65 death cases (65 cases in Hubei Province), 262 newly recovered cases (125 cases in Hubei Province), and 3971 suspected cases (1957 cases in Hubei Province).

As of 24:00 on [4 Feb 2020], the National Health and Health Commission has received a total of 24 324 confirmed cases (one reduction in Hainan Province) of confirmed cases, and 3219 of the severe cases, with cumulative deaths, in 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps. There were 490 deaths, and 892 cases recovered and were discharged (1 case each in Hainan Province and Hubei Province). There are 23 260 suspected cases.

At present, a total of 252 154 close contacts have been tracked, 18 457 medical observations have been lifted [today?], and 185 555 people are currently under medical observation.

A total of 39 confirmed cases were reported from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan: 18 in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (1 death), 10 in the Macao Special Administrative Region, and 11 in Taiwan.

