[Information on the nationalities and travel histories of these 10 confirmed cases of 2019-nCoV infection was not available at the time of preparation of this post (none of the more than 10 media reports available at the time had this information). One suspects that the only exposure may well have been presence on the boat where someone on a previous cruise on this same boat tested positive upon return to Hong Kong (gotten from a media report). According to the information, this individual was stated to have been asymptomatic until after the cruise. What is not clear is the actual definition of asymptomatic for this individual. In yesterday's [3 Feb 2020] update, we reported on another cruise ship with 3 2019-nCoV positive individuals (see Novel coronavirus (32): China, global, management, research 20200204.6950903, section [3]).

If no other high-risk exposure is identified, then it is likely there may have been transmission through fomites contaminating parts of the ship. We await further details surrounding this event. - Mod.MPP]

